# Cursor Rule – PRD Generator for AI Coding

## 1. Golden Rules (never violate)
- Every sentence must be **actionable** by an LLM.  
- No “think about”, “consider”, “maybe”. Use **imperative voice**.  
- One source of truth for: entities, endpoints, fields, business rules.  
- Scope is **single** deployable service (FastAPI + SQLite is fine).  

## 2. PRD Template (copy-paste → fill blanks)

```markdown
# Project: <ProjectName>

## 1. Elevator Pitch (1 line)
<One-sentence user value>

## 2. Core Entities
- <Entity>: <field1>:<type>, <field2>:<type>, …  
- …

## 3. API Surface (RESTful, no auth unless asked)
POST   /v1/<entities>        → create  
GET    /v1/<entities>        → list (pagination: page=1, size=20)  
GET    /v1/<entities>/{id}   → get single  
PATCH  /v1/<entities>/{id}   → update  
DELETE /v1/<entities>/{id}   → delete  

## 4. Business Rules
1. <Rule>  
2. …

## 5. Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All endpoints return JSON + Pydantic schema  
- [ ] Automatic OpenAPI docs reachable at /docs  
- [ ] `make test` runs ≥ 80 % coverage  
- [ ] ...

## 6. Tech & Run
- Stack: FastAPI, Pydantic v2, SQLite, pytest, uvicorn  
- Port: 8000  
- Env vars: none (use SQLite file db.sqlite3 in repo root)  